sentence: Looking at options trading activity among components of the S&P 500 index, there is noteworthy activity today in Home Depot Inc (Symbol: HD), where a total volume of 33,375 contracts has been traded thus far today, a contract volume which is representative of approximately 3.3 million underlying shares (given that every 1 contract represents 100 underlying shares).
That number works out to 76% of HD's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 4.4 million shares.
Especially high volume was seen for the $170 strike call option expiring December 15, 2017 , with 4,206 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 420,600 underlying shares of HD.

That number of contracts represents approximately 6.2 million underlying shares, working out to a sizeable 64.2% of KO's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 9.6 million shares.
Especially high volume was seen for the $44 strike call option expiring December 08, 2017 , with 28,672 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 2.9 million underlying shares of KO.
